# `docs/knowledge/` — memory layer README

Layer 5 of the five-layer design harness: **what the team has learned**. Organized by memory type — each file plays a specific role.

## Memory types used here

| File | Memory type | What it captures | Mutability |
|------|-------------|------------------|------------|
| `lessons/<domain>.md` | **episodic** | Dated narratives of what happened during specific work | Append-only; history is sacred (article §4e) |
| `decisions.md` | **procedural-chosen** | ADR-style: "we chose X over Y because Z" | Append-only; supersede with new entries, never edit old |
| `preferences.md` | **semantic-taste** | Stable taste calls the team holds | Mutable with team agreement |
| `ideations.md` | **speculative** | Open questions, unchosen paths, ideas we might revisit | Append-only; cross off when decided |
| `changelog.md` | **temporal** | When harness-structural changes happened (file renames, layer additions) | Append-only |
| `changelog.md` | **meta-log** | Which lessons promoted into AGENTS.md rules, and when | Append-only; created on first rule adoption (not at setup) |

The taxonomy comes from agent-memory research (OpenClaw / MemGPT / Generative Agents). Article §2.5 covers the mapping to the broader harness-memory model.

## Why separate files?

Each memory type has a different *lifecycle*:

- Episodic lessons decay in relevance with time but NEVER delete (history is sacred)
- Decisions supersede but don't edit (ADR discipline: v1 supersedes v0 as a new entry; v0 stays for audit trail)
- Preferences are the only mutable file — taste changes, we update
- Ideations cross off as ideas either graduate or get rejected
- Changelog is strictly temporal
- Rules is the meta-log: which lessons became rules

Mixing them in one big `lessons.md` collapses the lifecycles — you can't tell what to append to, what to revise, what to delete.

## How `/hd:maintain` interacts

- **`/hd:maintain capture`** appends to the right file based on content type:
  - Lesson-about-what-happened → `lessons/<domain>.md`
  - Decision-we-made → `decisions.md`
  - Taste-we-hold → `preferences.md`
  - Idea-we-might-pursue → `ideations.md`
  - User picks if ambiguous; skill auto-infers from tags when clear.
- **`/hd:maintain rule-propose <topic>`** reads `lessons/<domain>.md` files; proposes rule adoption when ≥ 3 same-topic episodes with a clean imperative.
- **`/hd:maintain rule-apply --plan-hash <sha>`** writes the rule to `AGENTS.md` + meta-entry to `changelog.md`. Source lessons are never touched.

## Split threshold

When any file exceeds ~15 entries, consider splitting by sub-domain. `/hd:maintain capture` surfaces the split suggestion when a file is approaching the threshold.

